            </div>
            <p>
              <a href="https://www.figma.com/proto/0saKDoJnmPwP5khhdecxfo/The-Cognitive-Design-Team-(CDT)?node-id=479-2059&starting-point-node-id=479%3A2059&t=jdjjzAPoEJ5YPeXG-1" target="_blank"><span class="underline">Link to prototype.</span></a><br><br><br>
              I updated and improved the e-commerce website to Norwegian dairy company TINE Handel. I worked as part of a team and followed the Design Thinking Process. Below is a very general overview:<br><br>
              <span class="bold">Empathy</span><br>
              Identified user research goals, planned and carried out primary and secondary research including interviews, a literature review and metadata. I then analysed results through affinity mapping and atomic research to find insights and make recommendations.<br><br>
              <span class="bold">Define</span><br>
              Created personas, made a user scenario and formulated a problem statement.<br><br>
              <span class="bold">Ideation</span><br>
              Planned and carried out ideation-workshops using techniques; brainstorming, sketchstorming, SCAMPER and MOSCOW. Created low fidelity prototypes and wireframes for both mobile and desktop interfaces. Considered user navigation and possible user journeys. Created wireflows and userflows.<br><br>
              <span class="bold">Prototyping</span><br>
              Used Figma to create medium and high-fidelity prototypes for mobile and desktop interfaces.<br><br>
              <span class="bold">Testing</span><br>
              Planned and carried out usability testing. Analysed results and created a usability testing report where recommendations were made to the next steps in developing the product.<br><br>
              <span class="bold">Learning points</span><br>
              This was a large project and I worked thoroughly throughout. As such I increased my understanding of, and ability to carry out, (the areas within) each stage of the design thinking process. The experience also made me more proficient in using Figma and I feel confident in creating new designs. Responsive design was also a key design solution to this project and I feel me knowledge of the use of responsive design has also improved. Also I have learnt the importance of a first audit to existing designs and, in regards to testing, making advance contact with good time in recruiting participants.
              <br><br>
              A link to a more detailed report of this project is
              <a href="https://www.figma.com/proto/JicM40iliaXSSCvvaFQUPR/TINE-Handel?type=design&node-id=1-81&t=h15ewHimjFRBBfbp-1&scaling=scale-down-width&page-id=0%3A1&mode=design" target="_blank"><span class="underline">here</span></a>.
